TI  == synthesis and evaluation of fluorogenic substrates for phospholipase d and phospholipase c.
AB  == fluorogenic analogues of phosphatidylcholine and lysophosphatidylcholine, ddpb and lysoddpb, were synthesized by an enzyme-assisted strategy. the analogues were evaluated as substrates for phospholipases c and d and lysophospholipase d. ddpb  was cleaved by bacterial and plant phospholipase d (pld) enzymes and represents the first direct fluorogenic substrate for real-time measurement of pld activity. both fluorogenic substrates have potential in screening for pld and pc-plc inhibitors and for monitoring spatiotemporal changes in pld activity in cells. [structure: see text]
