PMID== 16630975
TI  == bacterial contamination of nonsterile disposable gloves before use.
AB  == background: after bacillus cereus recovery in opened boxes of disposable gloves,  the bacteriological contamination of disposable nonsterile gloves kept stored in  native packages was investigated prospectively. methods: thirty-six commercially  available nonsterile nonpowdered disposable gloves made of latex, vinyl, or nitrile were cultured. results: a large variety of spore-forming and non-spore-forming bacteria was recovered, including bacillus cereus and clostridium perfringens. conclusion: this finding must be taken into consideration for care involving gloves in very immunocompromised patients.
