TI  == induction of ornithine decarboxylase by treatment of guinea pig lymphocytes with  phospholipase c.
AB  == treatment of guinea pig lymphocytes with clostridium perfringens phospholipase c  but not with naja naja snake venom phospholipase a2 increased ornithine decarboxylase activity. the increase in ornithine decarboxylase activity was suppressed by actinomycin d or cycloheximide, suggesting that de novo syntheses of rna and protein are necessary for the increase in the enzyme activity. these results suggest that the activation of phospholipase c rather than that of phospholipase a2 is responsible for induction of ornithine decarboxylase during lymphocyte transformation.
