PMID== 6322473
TI  == [relations between food poisoning and ascariasis].
AB  == during the examination of faeces for the causative agents of food poisoning, the  search was also extended to the occurrence of worm eggs. ascaris lumbricoides eggs occurred six times more frequently in persons affected with food poisoning than in consumers who were not harmed by the intake of poisoned food. this relationship was observed in non-specific cases of food poisoning and in those of unknown aetiology, whereas it was less pronounced in cases of specific poisoning. this difference has not been confirmed for trichuris trichiura. it is safe to say that ascaris infection increases the disposition to manifestation of symptoms of  intoxication and represents, among other things, a factor in the aetiology of food poisoning.
